South Africa's Dale Steyn is about to bowl on day 4 of the first Test match between South Africa and Sri Lanka held at the Kingsmead Stadium in Durban on February 16, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - Cricket South Africa has confirmed that Proteas fast bowler Dale Steyn has been ruled out of the Cricket World Cup on Tuesday. Steyn sustained a second shoulder injury following an initial injury which ruled him out of the tournament opener against hosts England and against Bangladesh. READ: Phehlukwayo hopeful SA can still survive World Cup He will be replaced by left-arm fast bowler Hendricks. The Proteas hope to overturn their World Cup fortunes following two consecutive defeats in the tournament. South Africa will play India on Wednesday. 